# workshop/migrations/{{.LedgerDir}} — the host-owned migration ledger

This directory is the host's own ordered migration stream. Gopernicus scaffolds
feature SQL into it (a store adapter's `ExportMigrations`), and from that moment
the files are **yours**: the framework never migrates at startup — the host
runner (`workshop/migrations`, `make migrate`) applies them pre-boot.

## Rules

- **Scaffold-and-own.** Once a migration lands here it is host-owned; edit and
  extend it as the host requires. Re-scaffolding a feature appends new files; it
  never rewrites files you already applied.
- **Never renumber.** Files apply in filename order under a 4-digit zero-padded
  prefix (`0001_...`, `0002_...`). The next migration is `max + 1`. Renumbering
  an already-applied file breaks the checksum ledger (`schema_migrations`).
- **`_`-prefixed files are skipped** by the runner — use them for scratch or
  manual SQL that must not enter the ledger.

## Usage
{{if .HasDB}}
```
gopernicus db create <slug>              # scaffold NNNN_<slug>.sql here (max+1)
make migrate                             # apply pending migrations pre-boot
go run ./workshop/migrations -status     # applied vs pending (file-only if the
                                         # database is unreachable)
```
{{- else}}
This host was scaffolded with `--db=none`, so no migration runner was emitted.
Re-run `gopernicus init --db=turso|pgx` (or add a connector plus a
`workshop/migrations` runner) to apply migrations from this ledger.
{{- end}}
